Heat a deep, heavy-bottomed pan, one-third filled with vegetable oil, until a breadcrumb will sizzle gently in it. (CAUTION: hot oil can be dangerous! Do not leave unattended.)Carefully add the tofu cubes to the oil and fry for 2-3 minutes or until golden and crisp. Remove using a slotted spoon and drain on kitchen towels.Heat the olive oil in a large non-stick frying pan. Add the chilli flakes and fry for 1-2 minutes.Add the red pepper and saut√© for 2-3 minutes to soften.Add the spinach leaves and mushrooms and cook gently until the spinach has wilted.Stir in the deep-fried tofu and cook until heated through.Transfer the tofu stir-fry to a warm bowl and serve at once.